## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

**Q1: Why is paternal preconception care important?**
A1: **Sperm carries health information for the child.** Paternal lifestyle choices can influence epigenetic information in sperm, potentially affecting the child's future health risks.

**Q2: What kind of diet is recommended for men?**
A2: **A balanced diet is crucial.** Avoiding high-fat foods and actively consuming vegetables, fruits, whole grains, and quality proteins is recommended to support sperm quality.

**Q3: When should men start preconception care?**
A3: **As soon as pregnancy is considered.** Sperm takes about 2-3 months to mature, so ideally, lifestyle changes should begin several months before planning conception.

